            <summary>What is Human Resource Management (HRM)?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
                Human Resource Management (HRM) is the process of managing an organization’s workforce,
                including hiring, employee records, attendance, payroll, performance, training, and compliance.
                HRM focuses on improving productivity while supporting employee growth and satisfaction.
            </div>
        </details>

        <details>
            <summary>What is an HR Management System (HRMS)?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
                An HRMS is a software application that combines many human resources functions, such as benefits administration, payroll, recruiting and training, and performance analysis and review into one package.
            </div>
        </details>

        <details>
            <summary>Is employee data secure in an HRMS?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
                Yes, modern HRMS platforms use enterprise-grade encryption, role-based access controls, and regular security audits to ensure sensitive employee information remains protected.
            </div>
        </details>

        <details>
            <summary>Who can use an HRMS?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
                HRMS platforms are designed for businesses of all sizes, from startups to large enterprises. They are used by HR professionals, managers, and employees through self-service portals.
            </div>
        </details>

